packages.name: autocfg
packages.description: Automatic cfg for Rust compiler features

packages.name: cc
packages.description:
A build-time dependency for Cargo build scripts to assist in invoking the native
C compiler to compile native C code into a static archive to be linked into Rust
code.

packages.name: libc
packages.description: Raw FFI bindings to platform libraries like libc.

packages.name: more-asserts
packages.description: Small library providing additional assert_* and debug_assert_* macros.

packages.name: num_threads
packages.description: A minimal library that determines the number of running threads for the current process.

packages.name: once_cell
packages.description: Single assignment cells and lazy values.

packages.name: proc-macro2
packages.description:
A substitute implementation of the compiler's `proc_macro` API to decouple
token-based libraries from the procedural macro use case.

packages.name: termcolor
packages.description: A simple cross platform library for writing colored text to a terminal.

packages.name: time
packages.description: Date and time library. Fully interoperable with the standard library. Mostly compatible with #![no_std].

packages.name: unicode-ident
packages.description: Determine whether characters have the XID_Start or XID_Continue properties according to Unicode Standard Annex #31

packages.name: winapi
packages.description: Raw FFI bindings for all of Windows API.

packages.description: Import libraries for the i686-pc-windows-gnu target. Please don't use this crate directly, depend on winapi instead.

packages.name: winapi-util
packages.description: A dumping ground for high level safe wrappers over winapi.

packages.name: winapi-x86_64-pc-windows-gnu
packages.description: Import libraries for the x86_64-pc-windows-gnu target. Please don't use this crate directly, depend on winapi instead.
